In this part, the thermophysical properties of both LFTFs and nanofluids are compared and discussed for particle volume concentration between 0.43 and 1.69%, and in the temperature range from 22 to 39 °C. The thermophysical properties of the LFTFs are reported by Karaipekli et al.44, while the thermophysical properties of the nanofluids are calculated based on different formulas commonly adopted in the literature. The nanofluid is considered as mixture of pure water and Al2O3 nanoparticles. The choice of this type of nanoparticle for the current study is based on the large set of data presented in the literature. Note that the thermal conductivity, specific heat, and density of Al2O3 nanoparticle are equal to 40 W/mK, 765 J/kg K, and 3970 kg/m3, respectively53.
